.TH JTUTIL-FOLD "1" "April 2026" "jtutil-fold manual" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
jtutil-fold \- Reorder a file by swapping address bits
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sorts the file by swapping two bits in the address.
Use when a memory is accessed with address bits swapped.
A typicial case is a video memory originally accessed as 8\-bit, that
is converted to 16\-bit. The bit given with \fB\-\-bit\fR will be used as the
new bit zero, effectively folding the data around it.
.SS "Usage:"
.IP
jtutil fold input\-file [output\-file] [flags]
.SS "Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-bit\fR int
bit number to swap with bit 0 (default 10)
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
help for fold
.SS "Global Flags:"
.TP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
Verbose
